Variables in Python
    A variable in Python is used to store data values so they can be reused and manipulated.

In data analytics, variables commonly store:
    1.Numeric values (sales, profit, age, scores)
    2.Text data (names, categories)
    3.Calculated results (average, total, growth rate)

Python is dynamically typed, meaning you don’t need to declare the type — Python understands it automatically.

Example (concept only, not code):
    Store total sales
    Store number of customers
    Store average revenue per customer

Variables make data readable, reusable, and analysable.
